<subSubSection id="25AD655A13135C4DFF15F984CEBDF907" pageId="23" pageNumber="476" type="description">
<paragraph id="6D0836D113135C4DFF15F984CEBDF907" blockId="23.[174,1232,1560,1714]" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Palaearctic and Oriental Regions (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013135C4DFCCCF984C93AF986" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[826,1071,1560,1587]" pageId="23" pageNumber="476" refId="ref19613" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Volume 1. Agromyzinae. Nagykovacsi, Pars Ltd., 1 - 416. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.18655 / Agromyzidae. Vol. 1." type="book" year="2015">Papp &amp; Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313135C4DFBB4F984C9C5F987" bold="true" box="[1090,1232,1560,1587]" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">
In 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113135C4DFB93F985C9DEF987" box="[1125,1227,1560,1586]" name="Ukraine" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
This “pestiferous … species” (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013135C4DFDFEF9A4CFEDF9E6" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[520,760,1592,1619]" pageId="23" pageNumber="476" refId="ref19613" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Volume 1. Agromyzinae. Nagykovacsi, Pars Ltd., 1 - 416. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.18655 / Agromyzidae. Vol. 1." type="book" year="2015">Papp &amp; Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
) hitherto has been sporadically found in 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313135C4DFF58F9C5CC78F9C7" box="[174,365,1624,1650]" country="Ukraine" name="Dnipropetrovs'k" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">Dnipropetrovsk</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313135C4DFE81F9C5CCC3F9C7" box="[375,470,1624,1650]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">Kharkiv</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313135C4DFDF9F9C5CF4DF9C7" box="[527,600,1624,1650]" country="Ukraine" name="Volyn'" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">Volyn</collectingRegion>
Regions in May and in 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313135C4DFC9AF9C5CED1F9C7" box="[876,964,1624,1650]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">Crimea</collectingRegion>
in September (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013135C4DFB85F9C5CDFFF926" author="Guglya, Yu." pageId="23" pageNumber="476" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref19059" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2011. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 1. 28 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 19 (2), 61 - 68 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2011">Guglya, 2011</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313135C4DFF08F9E5CCA5F927" box="[254,432,1656,1682]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313135C4DFE35F9E5CF59F926" bold="true" box="[451,588,1656,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="476">first record</emphasis>
). Only 5 ♂ and 
<specimenCount id="7BB1FD5813135C4DFCFCF9E4CE26F926" box="[778,819,1655,1683]" pageId="23" pageNumber="476" type="female">3 ♀</specimenCount>
are in the collection of KMUN. Its distribution and bionomics in Ukraine need further clarification.
</paragraph>
